## 4. Database Migration

**Not Applicable.** This is a client-side VS Code extension with no database.

## 5. Application Deployment

### 5.2 Method A: Automated Publish via GitHub Actions (Recommended)

| Step | Action | Command | Verification |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| 1 | Ensure all changes merged to main | git log --oneline -5 | Latest commit is the release commit |
| 2 | Update version in package.json | Edit version field | npm pkg get version returns correct version |
| 3 | Commit version bump | git commit -am "chore: bump version" | Commit in log |
| 4 | Create and push git tag | git tag v1.0.0 && git push origin v1.0.0 | Tag visible on GitHub |
| 5 | GitHub Actions triggers publish.yml | Automatic on tag push | Check Actions tab for green build |
| 6 | Verify VSIX artifact uploaded | GitHub Actions Artifacts | .vsix present |
| 7 | Verify Marketplace publish | VS Code Marketplace website | Extension visible and installable |
| 8 | Verify Open VSX publish | open-vsx.org | Extension visible and installable |

### 5.3 Method B: Manual Publish (Fallback)

1. npm ci — Install dependencies
2. npm run compile — Compile TypeScript
3. npx vsce package --no-dependencies — Package VSIX
4. npx vsce publish --packagePath \*.vsix -p <VSCE\_PAT> — Publish to Marketplace
5. npx ovsx publish \*.vsix -p <OVSX\_TOKEN> — Publish to Open VSX

### 5.4 Method C: Local VSIX Distribution (DEV/Testing)

1. code --install-extension kiro-sdlc-agents-1.0.0.vsix — Install locally
2. code --list-extensions | grep kiro-sdlc-agents — Verify installation

## 6. Configuration Changes

### 6.1 GitHub Repository Secrets

| Secret Name | Description |
| --- | --- |
| VSCE\_PAT | VS Code Marketplace Personal Access Token |
| OVSX\_TOKEN | Open VSX Registry API Token |

### 6.2 Extension Settings (User-Facing)

| Setting | Type | Default | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| kiroSdlc.autoIndex | boolean | true | Auto-run code indexer after injection |
| kiroSdlc.preferredIndexer | enum | "auto" | Preferred indexer runtime |

## 7. Post-Deployment Verification

### 7.1 Health Checks

| Check | Method | Expected Result |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Extension activates | Open VS Code | No errors in Extension Host output |
| Commands registered | Command Palette | All 5 commands visible |
| Status bar visible | Bottom-right | Icon + text visible |
| Marketplace listing | Visit URL | Extension page loads |

### 7.2 Smoke Tests

| # | Scenario | Expected Result |
| --- | --- | --- |
| 1 | Extension activates on startup | Status bar shows, no errors |
| 2 | Inject All command works | Confirmation → files injected → success |
| 3 | Status command works | Shows component status |
| 4 | Confirmation dialog blocks | Cancel = no files modified |
| 5 | No workspace error | Error message shown |

## 8. Rollback Plan

### 8.2 Rollback Decision Criteria

| Condition | Action |
| --- | --- |
| Extension crashes VS Code | Immediate unpublish |
| Commands throw errors | Publish previous version |
| Silent activation failure | Hotfix patch |
| Minor UI issue | Fix in next patch |

### 8.3 Rollback Steps

| Step | Action | Verification |
| --- | --- | --- |
| 1 | Unpublish broken version | Marketplace shows removed |
| 2 | Checkout previous tag | Source matches previous release |
| 3 | Build previous version | VSIX created |
| 4 | Publish previous version | Previous version live |
| 5 | Verify rollback | Previous behavior restored |

### 8.4 Rollback Time Estimate: ~20 minutes

## 9. Environment-Specific Notes

### 9.1 DEV

* Install from .vsix file locally
* Use F5 for debugging

### 9.2 BETA

* Publish with --pre-release flag
* Monitor GitHub Issues

### 9.3 PROD (Marketplace)

* Deployment Window: Any time
* Approval: Dev Lead + QA Lead
* Propagation: ~5-10 minutes

### 9.4 PROD (Open VSX)

* Published simultaneously via GitHub Actions
* Serves Kiro IDE users

